…suspends issuance of visa on arrival to travellers The federal government has banned flights from 13 countries with over 1,000 covid-19 cases domestically. The countries include China, Italy, Iran, South Korea, Spain, Japan, France, Germany, United States of America, Norway, United Kingdom, Netherlands & Switzerland This was disclosed by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), through its twitter handle. The NCDC said the federal government has also suspended the issuance of visa on arrival to travellers from these countries, adding that all travelers returning from these countries prior to the restriction will be in supervised self-isolation, monitored by NCDC and Port Health Services. More details shortly…. 